gurmukhi: ਸਰਬ ਭੁਗਤਾ ਸਰਬ ਦੰਡਣ ਸਰਬ ਕਰਮ ਅਧੀਨ ॥੧੫॥੧੯੫॥
transliteration: Sarab Khanndan Sarab Danndan Sarab Karam Adheen||15195||
translation: He is the Destroyer and Punisher of all and keeps all the works under His control.15.195.

gurmukhi: ਸਰਬ ਸਿੰਮ੍ਰਿਤਨ ਸਰਬ ਸਾਸਤ੍ਰਨ ਸਰਬ ਬੇਦ ਬਿਚਾਰ ॥
transliteration: Sarab Sinmritan Sarab Saastran Sarab Bed Bichaar||
translation: He is not within the contemplation of all the Smritis, all the Shastras and all the Vedas.

gurmukhi: ਦੁਸਟ ਹਰਤਾ ਬਿਸ੍ਵ ਭਰਤਾ ਅਾਦਿ ਰੂਪ ਅਪਾਰ ॥
transliteration: Doust Hartaa Bisva Bhartaa Aadh Roop Apaar||
translation: He, the Infinite Primal Entity is the Vanquisher of the tyrants and the Sustainer of the universe.

gurmukhi: ਦੁਸਟ ਦੰਡਣ ਪੁਸਟ ਖੰਡਣ ਅਾਦਿ ਦੇਵ ਅਖੰਡ ॥
transliteration: Doust Danndan Poust Khanndan Aadh Dev Akhannd||
translation: He, the Primal Indivisible Lord is the punisher of the tyrants and breaker of the ego of the mighty.

gurmukhi: ਭੂਮ ਅਕਾਸ ਜਲੇ ਥਲੇ ਮਹਿ ਜਪਤ ਜਾਪ ਅਮੰਡ ॥੧੬॥੧੯੬॥
transliteration: Bhoom Akaas Jale Thale Maih Japat Jaap Amannd||16||196||
translation: The name of that Uninstalled Lord is being repeated by the beings of earth, sky, water and land.16.196.
All the pious thoughts of the world known through the medium of knowledge.

gurmukhi: ਅਾਦਿ ਦੇਵ ਅਪਾਰ ਸ੍ਰੀ ਪਤਿ ਦੁਸਟ ਪੁਸਟ ਪ੍ਹਾਰ ॥
transliteration: Aadh Dev Apaar Sroo Pat(i) Doust Poust Prahaar||
translation: They are all within that Infinite Primal Lord of maya, the Destroyer of mighty tyrants.

gurmukhi: ਅੰਨ ਦਾਤਾ ਗਿਅਾਨ ਗਿਅਾਤਾ ਸਰਬ ਮਾਨ ਮਹਿੰਦ੍ਰ ॥
transliteration: Ann Daataa Giaan Giaataa Sarab Maan Mahindra||
translation: He is the Donor of Sustenance, the Knower of Knowledge and the Sovereign revered by all.

gurmukhi: ਬੇਦ ਬਿਅਾਸ ਕਰੇ ਕੲੀ ਦਿਨ ਕੋਟਿ ੲਿੰਦ੍ਰ ੳੁਪਿੰਦ੍ਰ ॥੧੭॥੧੯੭॥
transliteration: Bed Biaas Dare Kaee Din Kottee Indra Oupindra||17||197||
translation: He hath Created many Ved Vyas and millions of Indras and other gods.17.197.

gurmukhi: ਜਨਮ ਜਾਤਾ ਕਰਮ ਗਿਅਾਤਾ ਧਰਮ ਚਾਰ ਬਿਚਾਰ ॥
transliteration: Janam Jaataa Karam Giaataa Dharam Chaar Bichaar||
translation: He is the cause of birth and knower of actions and notions of beauteous religious discipline.

gurmukhi: ਬੇਦ ਭੇਵ ਨ ਪਾਵਨੀ ਸਿਵ ਰੁਦ੍ਰ ਅੌਰ ਮੁਖਚਾਰ ॥
transliteration: Bed Bhev Na Paavaee Siv Rudra Aur Moukhchaar||
translation: But the Vedas, Shiva, Rudra and Brahma could not Know His mystery and the secret of His notions.

gurmukhi: ਕੋਟਿ ੲਿੰਦ੍ਰ ੳੁਪਿੰਦ੍ਰ ਬਿਅਾਸ ਸਨਕ ਸਨਤ ਕੁਮਾਰ ॥
transliteration: Kottee Indra Oupindra Biaas Sanak Sanat Koumaar||
translation: Milions of Indras and other subordinate gods, Vyas, Sanak and Sanat Kumar.

gurmukhi: ਗਾੲਿ ਗਾੲਿ ਥਕੇ ਸਭੈ ਗੁਨ ਚੱਕ੍ਰਤ ਭੇ ਮੁਖਚਾਰ ॥੧੮॥੧੯੮॥
transliteration: Gade Gade Thake Sabbai Goun Chakkrat Bhe Moukhchaar||18||198||
translation: They and Brahma have got tired of singing His Praises in state of astonishment.18.198.

gurmukhi: ਅਾਦਿ ਅੰਤ ਨ ਮਧ ਜਾ ਕੋ ਭੂਤ ਭੱਬ ਭਵਾਨ ॥
transliteration: Aadh Ant Na Madh Jaa Ko Bhoot Bhabb Bhavaan||
translation: He is devoid of beginning, middle and end and also of past, present and future.
